records.addlTxt:
Defendant Darnell Lamonte Harris in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Marissa Luz Santiago appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant sentenced to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, concurrent with COUNT 2, but consecutive with any other sentence, with credit for 3 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. for school/treatment/child care to apply.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
* Court sets restitution at $0.
* Court costs and victim/witness surcharges to be paid during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment;
* Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment; 
* AODA assessment and any recommended treatment;
* Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers;
* No alcohol or controlled substances;
* Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any counseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications;
* Maintain employment or be attending school;
* Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program;
* Successfully complete a Parenting Program;
* No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

